      <div class="bio-content">
        <h1>Siberian Tiger</h1>
        <p class="status endangered big">Endangered</p>
        <p><strong>Estimated remaining:</strong> ~500</p>

        <h3>Habitat</h3>
        <p>Boreal forests (taiga) of the Russian Far East and Northeast China, characterized by cold winters, deep snow, and mixed coniferous-deciduous forests with rugged terrain.</p>

        <h3>Threats</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Poaching for traditional medicine</li>
          <li>Habitat loss from logging and development</li>
          <li>Prey depletion (deer and wild boar)</li>
          <li>Infrastructure development fragmenting habitat</li>
          <li>Genetic isolation of small populations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Conservation efforts</h3>
        <p>Russia's strict anti-poaching laws and protected areas like Sikhote-Alin Biosphere Reserve. Transboundary cooperation with China. Prey population enhancement programs. Winter patrols to combat poaching in snow-covered areas.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
